SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 120
BY SENATOR HODGES
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Louisiana's Jewish-Americans on their contributions to
the state and nation, recognizes Jewish-American Heritage Month, and encourages
observance of Shabbat on May 15-16, 2026, as a time of prayer, reflection, gratitude, and
thanksgiving to Almighty God in celebration of the 250th Anniversary of our nation.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Louisiana's Jewish-American citizens for their contributions to the state and
3 nation, to recognize May 2026 as Jewish-American Heritage Month in Louisiana,
4 and to join with other states in encouraging Christians and persons of all faith
5 traditions to join with their Jewish neighbors in observing a Shabbat from sundown
6 on May 15, 2026, through nightfall on May 16, 2026, as a time of prayer, reflection,
7 gratitude, and thanksgiving to Almighty God in celebration of the upcoming 250th
8 anniversary of the United States.
9 WHEREAS, on May 4, 2026, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation
10 recognizing May 2026 as Jewish-American Heritage Month; calling upon the nation, in
11 anticipation of the 250th anniversary of the United States of America, to observe a national
12 Shabbat from sundown on May 15, 2026, through nightfall on May 16, 2026, as a time of
13 prayer, reflection, rest, gratitude, and thanksgiving to Almighty God, and as an opportunity
14 for families and communities to gather in recognition of the blessings of faith, freedom, and
15 national unity; and
16 WHEREAS, Jewish-Americans have contributed immeasurably to the cultural,
17 economic, scientific, educational, military, and civic development of the United States since
18 the founding of the nation; and
